    "what_description": "Euploca foliata is an evergreen shrub native to the tropical regions of Central and South America. It belongs to the family Boraginaceae, a group of plants commonly known as borage or forget-me-not family. Botanically, Euploca foliata has simple, opposite, and elliptical-shaped leaves that are 2-6 cm long and 1-4 cm wide, with a leathery texture and entire margin. The plant produces small, white, or pale blue flowers in axillary clusters, with a 5-lobed calyx and a corolla that is 5-7 mm in diameter. Its stem is woody, brown, and glabrous, with a height range of 1-3 meters.",
